**A debounce function ensures a given function is only called after a specified delay has passed without it being invoked again.**

```javascript
// Debounce function
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example usage:
function handleResize() {
  console.log('Window resized!');
}

window.addEventListener('resize', debounce(handleResize, 300));
```

*In this example, `handleResize` will only log once 300ms after the user stops resizing the window.*
